<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3872&amp;p=31328#p31328"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Which games had the best instruments (using APU sound only)?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3872&amp;p=31328#p31328"><![CDATA[
I've always loved the US SMB2's music. The nice, dreamy, piano-like instrument used in a few of the tracks (notably the title theme, and most of the main overworld theme) was a marked improvement over the very boring square waves of Doki Doki Panic. It was just one of many nice touches that transformed what could have been another ordinary FDS port into something special. Definitely one of Nintendo's finest accomplishments in my book.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=935">BMF54123</a> — Fri Feb 29, 2008 12:16 am</p><hr />
